Experiment 7
AIM
To develop an application using POSIX threads (pthreads) in C for concurrent execution of multiple 
threads.
ALGORITHM
Algorithm for Main Function
1. Start the program. 
2. Declare two thread variables. 
3. Initialize thread numbers. 
4. Create two threads using pthread_create(). 
5. Wait for both threads using pthread_join(). 
6. Display completion message. 
7. Stop the program. 
Algorithm for Thread Function
1. Receive thread number as argument. 
2. Display the running thread message. 
3. Terminate the thread. 
PROGRAM
#include<stdio.h>
#include<pthread.h>
void* msg(void* n){
printf("Thread %d is running\n",*(int*)n);
return NULL;
}
int main(){
pthread_t t1,t2;
int a=1,b=2;
pthread_create(&t1,NULL,msg,&a);
pthread_create(&t2,NULL,msg,&b);
pthread_join(t1,NULL);
pthread_join(t2,NULL);
printf("Both threads finished execution\n");
return 0;
}
OUTPUT
Thread 1 is running
Thread 2 is running
Both threads finished execution
RESULT
Thus, an application using POSIX threads (pthreads) in C was successfully developed and executed for 
concurrent thread execution
